Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4E6AF1F7189C8B1753B1DD" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1806" box="[2276,2387,2770,2799]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="181" pageNumber="943" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4E6AF1F8259CA016D6B024" baseAuthorityName="Lataste" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[2009,2262,2809,2838]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="181" pageNumber="943" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atacamensis">Myotis atacamensis</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4E6AF1F78E9D44171BB00C" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1838" box="[2162,2331,2845,2878]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="181" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chiloensis">M. chiloensis</taxonomicName>
, but studies based on morphology and molecular data indicate clear distinction between the two.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF4E6AF1F8259DCF1675B081" blockId="181.[2007,2602,2651,3075]" box="[2009,2165,2966,2995]" pageId="181" pageNumber="943">Monotypic.</paragraph>
